NRC: Glossary --
Light water reactor
 Index | Site Map | FAQ | Help | Glossary | Contact Us         Advanced Search U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission Home Who We Are What We Do Nuclear Reactors Nuclear Materials Radioactive Waste Facility Info Finder Public Involvement Electronic Reading Room Home > Electronic Reading Room > Basic References > Glossary > Light water reactor Light water reactor A term used to describe reactors using ordinary water as coolant, including boiling water reactors (BWRs) and pressurized water reactors (PWRs), the most common types used in the United States. Privacy Policy | Site Disclaimer Last revised Monday, June 23, 2003